The California home of a Christian pop singer was spared in wildfires that consumed parts of San Diego County last week, and, naturally, she's chalking it up as a miracle.

'It’s a total miracle ’cause the wind changed right when the fires were about to take over our house,' Christian singer Rebecca St. James wrote in a Facebook post accompanying a photo of the charred landscape that ends just feet from her patio.

St. James and her family were forced to evacuate the home on Wednesday as the flames approached her neighborhood. 

