Additional evacuations were ordered on Thursday, with about 21,000 people being forced to leave their homes because of the widlfires.

Several California State University students were amongst those forced to evacuate - even as the students were in the middle of finals week. 

California Governor Jerry Brown declared a state of emergency in San Diego County as fires have scorched more than 20,000 acres.

